From: Zheng Qixing <zhengqixing@huawei.com>
Date: Sat, 12 Apr 2025 17:25:54 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] block: fix resource leak in blk_register_queue() error path
Git-commit: 40f2eb9b531475dd01b683fdaf61ca3cfd03a51e
Patch-mainline: v6.15-rc3
References: CVE-2025-37980 bsc#1243522

[ Adapted backport. The cleanup after failure of elv_register_queue() does the
  reverse of the call in "if (q->mq_ops)", the same one as would be done in
  blk_unregister_queue() in case the registration succeeded. ]

When registering a queue fails after blk_mq_sysfs_register() is
successful but the function later encounters an error, we need
to clean up the blk_mq_sysfs resources.

Add the missing blk_mq_sysfs_unregister() call in the error path
to properly clean up these resources and prevent a memory leak.

Fixes: 320ae51feed5 ("blk-mq: new multi-queue block IO queueing mechanism")
Signed-off-by: Zheng Qixing <zhengqixing@huawei.com>
Reviewed-by: Christoph Hellwig <hch@lst.de>
Reviewed-by: Yu Kuai <yukuai3@huawei.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250412092554.475218-1-zhengqixing@huaweicloud.com
Signed-off-by: Jens Axboe <axboe@kernel.dk>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 block/blk-sysfs.c |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/block/blk-sysfs.c
+++ b/block/blk-sysfs.c
@@ -992,6 +992,8 @@ int blk_register_queue(struct gendisk *d
 			kobject_uevent(&q->kobj, KOBJ_REMOVE);
 			kobject_del(&q->kobj);
 			blk_trace_remove_sysfs(dev);
+			if (q->mq_ops)
+				blk_mq_unregister_dev(dev, q);
 			kobject_put(&dev->kobj);
 			return ret;
 		}
